1
00:00:02,508 --> 00:00:03,907
BARBIE:
Two weeks ago,

2
00:00:04,076 --> 00:00:06,510
an invisible dome
crashed down on Chester's Mill,

3
00:00:06,679 --> 00:00:08,579
cutting us off
from the rest of the world.

4
00:00:08,747 --> 00:00:11,079
Why the dome is here,
or what mysteries lie ahead

5
00:00:11,250 --> 00:00:14,686
we still don't know.
Every day it tests our limits,

6
00:00:14,853 --> 00:00:17,413
bringing out the best
and the worst in us.

7
00:00:19,725 --> 00:00:21,317
Some say
we'll be stuck here forever.

8
00:00:22,094 --> 00:00:25,860
But we will never stop fighting
to find a way out.

9
00:00:26,599 --> 00:00:28,396
You're the one
tearing Chester's Mill apart.

10
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:30,034
The dome wants Jim dead.

11
00:00:30,469 --> 00:00:33,836
I'm looking for someone.
She's about 17. long dark hair, tall.

12
00:00:35,107 --> 00:00:37,075
- Can I help you with something?
- Linda!

13
00:00:39,211 --> 00:00:42,305
Heard you lost your house,
my home is your home.

14
00:00:42,481 --> 00:00:43,914
He's a liar and a murderer.

15
00:00:44,083 --> 00:00:45,516
We can still stop him.

16
00:00:45,684 --> 00:00:47,777
Those surges fried
most of our power sources.

17
00:00:47,953 --> 00:00:49,633
Who knows what other damage
they've caused?

18
00:00:49,788 --> 00:00:52,985
I've got to survey our water supply
and find another source of power.

19
00:00:53,158 --> 00:00:56,093
Fire tower magnet got us through the
day, but I'm not gonna sleep tonight.

20
00:00:56,262 --> 00:00:59,595
JULIA: You think that's what stopped
the surges and cleared the dome?

21
00:00:59,765 --> 00:01:01,562
What else could it have been?

22
00:01:02,234 --> 00:01:03,701
Are you okay?

23
00:01:03,869 --> 00:01:05,496
[SCREAMS]

24
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:33,498
I...

25
00:01:34,099 --> 00:01:35,930
...missed
- Ha-ha-ha.

26
00:01:36,302 --> 00:01:38,099
This.

27
00:01:38,370 --> 00:01:40,133
Me too.

28
00:01:40,306 --> 00:01:43,469
Almost as much
as I'm gonna miss coffee.

29
00:01:44,843 --> 00:01:46,105
- Really?
- Ha-ha-ha.

30
00:01:48,314 --> 00:01:50,509
Oh, unh.

31
00:01:51,784 --> 00:01:55,049
Seriously, Mr. Barbara,

32
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:58,383
if you think I'm gonna get by
under this thing without you...

33
00:02:39,631 --> 00:02:43,727
I thought the Big Jim slumber party
was just a nightmare.

34
00:02:44,770 --> 00:02:45,794
[SIGHS]

35
00:02:45,971 --> 00:02:46,995
Worse.

36
00:02:47,172 --> 00:02:49,299
- We can't wake up from it.
- Great.

37
00:02:49,475 --> 00:02:50,999
Now that your house is trashed,

38
00:02:51,176 --> 00:02:54,168
looks like we're stuck on Elm Street
for a while longer.

39
00:02:54,346 --> 00:02:55,711
Angie never came home last night.

40
00:02:55,881 --> 00:02:58,611
Can't blame her. She probably
sacked out at the Sweetbriar

41
00:02:58,784 --> 00:03:00,445
to stay away from the Big Bad Wolf.

42
00:03:00,619 --> 00:03:03,520
JIM:
Kids, breakfast is ready.

43
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:06,087
Hey, good morning, you two.

44
00:03:06,558 --> 00:03:08,890
Grab something to drink
out of the fridge there.

45
00:03:09,061 --> 00:03:11,689
Dome sapped my generator,
so everything's going bad.

46
00:03:12,531 --> 00:03:15,159
Cooked you up some breakfast,
sit down, plenty to eat.

47
00:03:15,634 --> 00:03:17,761
Come on. Have a seat.

48
00:03:18,871 --> 00:03:20,202
There you go.

49
00:03:20,372 --> 00:03:22,306
Now, from what I understand,

50
00:03:22,474 --> 00:03:24,408
you all seem to know
a lot about this dome

51
00:03:26,512 --> 00:03:29,538
- and I can't wait to hear all about it.
- Since when do you care?

52
00:03:31,383 --> 00:03:34,011
Well, since the dome
spared my life yesterday,

53
00:03:34,186 --> 00:03:35,551
I've become more of a believer.

54
00:03:35,721 --> 00:03:38,241
Don't you have to go round up
some more generators or something?

55
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:41,553
- Ha-ha-ha.
PHIL: Jim? You read?

56
00:03:41,727 --> 00:03:44,560
Patterson's roof just caved in
from yesterday's damage.

57
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:47,563
All right, thanks, Phil.
I'm heading into town now.

58
00:03:47,966 --> 00:03:49,797
Enjoy.

59
00:03:50,068 --> 00:03:51,763
We'll continue
this conversation later.

60
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:25,734
Junior, this hellhole really more
comfortable than your own bed?

61
00:04:28,307 --> 00:04:31,242
I'd rather sleep here
than under the roof of a murderer.

62
00:04:31,410 --> 00:04:33,071
Get that hangover of yours
out of bed.

63
00:04:33,245 --> 00:04:36,942
I need you to go over to the school
and open it up.

64
00:04:37,816 --> 00:04:40,444
Rebecca Pine
is gonna start classes again.

65
00:04:40,619 --> 00:04:43,554
You really think people care about
calculus and social studies anymore?

66
00:04:43,722 --> 00:04:45,485
She's gonna teach things
that matter.

67
00:04:45,657 --> 00:04:47,938
Things that are gonna help this town
get back on its feet.

68
00:04:48,093 --> 00:04:52,120
Now, I need you to get over there,
open it up, clean up any mess.

69
00:04:52,297 --> 00:04:54,356
- Do it yourself.
- Hey.

70
00:04:55,634 --> 00:04:58,228
I risked my life for you yesterday.

71
00:05:00,506 --> 00:05:02,371
Least you could do
is lend me a hand.

72
00:05:04,009 --> 00:05:06,569
I'll do it for the town, not for you.

73
00:06:26,058 --> 00:06:29,789
Didn't know running the town meant
waiting on it too. Where's Angie?

74
00:06:29,962 --> 00:06:31,725
I don't know.
She was a no-show this morning.

75
00:06:32,230 --> 00:06:34,198
Couple people say
that when they came to,

76
00:06:34,366 --> 00:06:37,858
they saw you
with a noose around your neck.

77
00:06:38,937 --> 00:06:40,131
It's a long story, Andrea.

78
00:06:40,305 --> 00:06:44,207
People say it was you who ended
all that magnetism business.

79
00:06:44,910 --> 00:06:47,879
Well, if anyone saved us,
it was the good Lord.

80
00:06:48,914 --> 00:06:50,279
I don't think so.

81
00:06:50,449 --> 00:06:54,249
You were the one
willing to sacrifice himself,

82
00:06:54,419 --> 00:06:56,546
that's why the dome spared us.

83
00:06:56,722 --> 00:07:01,682
The only reason this town is still
standing is because of Big Jim Rennie.

84
00:07:02,928 --> 00:07:04,555
- Hey, good morning.
- Good morning.

85
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:06,789
- Coffee?
- Sure.

86
00:07:06,965 --> 00:07:10,332
It's the least I could do
to pay you back.

87
00:07:10,869 --> 00:07:15,101
Just want you to know, I have no,
uh, animosity toward you, Julia.

88
00:07:15,273 --> 00:07:18,572
I have nothing but deep gratitude.

89
00:07:18,744 --> 00:07:21,076
That sounded dangerously close
to a thank-you.

90
00:07:21,647 --> 00:07:22,671
BARBIE:
Gratitude?

91
00:07:22,848 --> 00:07:25,282
That's a word I thought
would never come out of your mouth.

92
00:07:28,186 --> 00:07:29,619
- Jim?
JIM: Hey.

93
00:07:30,188 --> 00:07:31,985
We have a little emergency.

94
00:07:36,194 --> 00:07:38,788
I don't know if it's because
of our isolated ecosystem

95
00:07:38,964 --> 00:07:40,397
or the magnetic fluctuations,

96
00:07:40,565 --> 00:07:43,693
but something has caused our butterfly
reproductive cycle to accelerate.

97
00:07:43,869 --> 00:07:47,305
Killer butterflies, huh? Now we really
got something to worry about.

98
00:07:47,472 --> 00:07:50,566
Yeah, I know it doesn't sound serious,
but butterflies lay eggs.

99
00:07:50,742 --> 00:07:52,835
And those eggs
turn into caterpillars.

100
00:07:53,011 --> 00:07:56,174
Caterpillars who are
very, very hungry.

101
00:07:56,348 --> 00:07:58,373
These creatures can eat 200 times
their own weight.

102
00:07:58,550 --> 00:07:59,847
And they are not being choosy.

103
00:08:00,385 --> 00:08:02,444
Off my initial survey,
more than half our crops

104
00:08:02,621 --> 00:08:04,316
are already infested with caterpillars.

105
00:08:16,668 --> 00:08:18,727
Angie's dead.

106
00:08:27,045 --> 00:08:30,242
- Oh, my Lord.
- Lock on the back door was broken.

107
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,742
What are you doing here?

108
00:08:34,853 --> 00:08:37,048
Guys, check that locker,
because the handprint shows

109
00:08:37,222 --> 00:08:39,383
that she was reaching for it.

110
00:08:42,127 --> 00:08:43,219
Let's get busy.

111
00:08:49,801 --> 00:08:51,401
Is this where
you point the finger at me?

112
00:08:52,337 --> 00:08:54,498
You and I have both done things
we're not proud of.

113
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:57,721
Neither of us
would do something like this.

114
00:08:58,009 --> 00:08:59,442
So then who would?

115
00:08:59,611 --> 00:09:01,044
JIM:
I got no idea.

116
00:09:01,213 --> 00:09:04,774
But whoever murdered her is walking
around Chester's Mill right now.

117
00:09:05,484 --> 00:09:07,418
And I need your help
hunting them down.

118
00:09:09,121 --> 00:09:11,180
PHIL:
Jim. Found something.

119
00:09:15,427 --> 00:09:20,023
The killer stepped in their dirty work,
left us a gift.

120
00:09:22,334 --> 00:09:24,393
So quiet out here.

121
00:09:24,636 --> 00:09:26,968
It's, like, the only place
that feels normal.

122
00:09:27,139 --> 00:09:31,235
Yeah, like we could forget
there's a giant plastic bowl over us.

123
00:09:31,409 --> 00:09:32,603
Hey, poison ivy.

124
00:09:34,946 --> 00:09:37,437
Not a big problem in L.A., I guess.

125
00:09:52,664 --> 00:09:54,655
They're butterflies.

126
00:09:56,434 --> 00:09:59,130
NORRIE: They're dead.
- It's okay.

127
00:09:59,304 --> 00:10:01,534
There's about to be
a lot more of them.

128
00:10:01,706 --> 00:10:03,833
How do you know that?

129
00:10:04,743 --> 00:10:09,112
If they're dying,
then they laid new eggs.

130
00:10:09,281 --> 00:10:10,509
Their life cycle's over.

131
00:10:10,682 --> 00:10:12,274
[GIRL GROANING]

132
00:10:15,587 --> 00:10:17,919
NORRIE: Who is she?
JOE: I've never seen her before.

133
00:10:18,456 --> 00:10:20,287
Are you okay?

134
00:10:21,459 --> 00:10:23,154
Hey, what's your name?

135
00:10:23,595 --> 00:10:25,256
I don't know.

136
00:10:26,765 --> 00:10:28,130
How long have you been out here?

137
00:10:29,701 --> 00:10:30,929
Hey, give me a hand.

138
00:10:31,403 --> 00:10:32,870
All right.

139
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,706
You have to let her go, son.

140
00:10:45,851 --> 00:10:48,649
Takes time
for the numbness to wear off.

141
00:10:51,256 --> 00:10:55,056
I need you to tell me, James,
did you do this?

142
00:10:55,927 --> 00:10:57,360
How can you say that?

143
00:10:57,529 --> 00:10:59,009
Because I know how much
you loved her.

144
00:10:59,164 --> 00:11:01,223
It wouldn't be the first time
it took an ugly turn.

145
00:11:01,399 --> 00:11:03,230
Angie meant everything to me.

146
00:11:03,401 --> 00:11:05,481
And not having her
drove you to do some crazy things.

147
00:11:05,637 --> 00:11:08,367
Just tell me the truth
and I'll take care of this.

148
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,399
Angie wanted you dead.

149
00:11:12,177 --> 00:11:14,543
What happened? She come
after you and you got to her first?

150
00:11:15,247 --> 00:11:19,047
- What are you talking about?
- Did you do it? Did you kill her?

151
00:11:19,351 --> 00:11:21,071
I'd never hurt
someone close to you, Junior.

152
00:11:21,219 --> 00:11:22,846
No, no, no. I don't believe you.

153
00:11:23,021 --> 00:11:25,181
You killed Angie
and now you're trying to pin it on me.

154
00:11:25,323 --> 00:11:29,123
- Junior, I would never do anything to...
- If you killed Angie, I'll make you suffer!

155
00:11:33,365 --> 00:11:36,459
We're crashing at Big Jim's.
We can take you there.

156
00:11:37,135 --> 00:11:38,898
[PEOPLE CHATTERING QUIETLY]

157
00:12:01,059 --> 00:12:03,357
What's going on? Tell me.

158
00:12:03,929 --> 00:12:04,953
Is it Angie?

159
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:11,094
Barbie, is Angie okay?

160
00:12:17,909 --> 00:12:19,467
I'm sorry, Joe.

161
00:12:21,513 --> 00:12:24,971
She's dead.
Someone killed her? Why?

162
00:12:25,884 --> 00:12:26,942
BARBIE:
I don't know.

163
00:12:27,118 --> 00:12:30,178
Whoever did this is going to pay.

164
00:12:37,395 --> 00:12:39,295
How's Joe doing?

165
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:43,264
He's a tough kid.

166
00:12:45,570 --> 00:12:48,061
I'm worried he's bottling it all up.

167
00:12:49,407 --> 00:12:51,398
Well, he's in shock.

168
00:12:51,609 --> 00:12:53,270
I've seen it a lot in the field.

169
00:12:54,079 --> 00:12:56,070
You know, gotta just take time
to process things.

170
00:12:56,247 --> 00:12:58,112
I can't believe she's gone.

171
00:12:58,283 --> 00:13:00,046
First we lose Linda, now Angie.

172
00:13:00,218 --> 00:13:02,018
I thought the dome was supposed
to protect us.

173
00:13:02,153 --> 00:13:05,418
No, it's up to us
to protect each other.

174
00:13:05,657 --> 00:13:07,022
Come here.

175
00:13:11,296 --> 00:13:13,628
- So you know her?
- Yeah.

176
00:13:13,798 --> 00:13:17,131
She's the girl I rescued
from the lake yesterday.

177
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:23,098
She ran off
and we took her to Sam's cabin.

178
00:13:24,275 --> 00:13:27,301
- What do you know about her?
- Nothing.

179
00:13:27,479 --> 00:13:29,743
She doesn't remember who she is

180
00:13:29,914 --> 00:13:32,041
or even if she has a family here.

181
00:13:32,751 --> 00:13:34,048
Why?

182
00:13:34,219 --> 00:13:38,212
Phil found a girl's bloody shoeprint
at the scene.

183
00:13:39,924 --> 00:13:41,619
What are you getting at?

184
00:13:42,127 --> 00:13:44,687
Well, she's found hiding out,

185
00:13:44,863 --> 00:13:46,956
she's scraped up,
she's clearly upset.

186
00:13:47,132 --> 00:13:48,724
Nobody's seen her before.

187
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:51,801
She is a scared little girl.

188
00:13:51,970 --> 00:13:53,733
There's no way
she could have killed Angie.

189
00:13:53,905 --> 00:13:55,372
You can't be sure of that.

190
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:57,838
I wanna find who did this
as much as anyone,

191
00:13:58,009 --> 00:13:59,977
but just because no one's
ever seen her before

192
00:14:00,145 --> 00:14:01,578
doesn't mean that she's guilty.

193
00:14:01,746 --> 00:14:03,976
Doesn't make her innocent, either.

194
00:14:04,149 --> 00:14:07,084
There's something about her,
like I've...

195
00:14:08,686 --> 00:14:11,519
I've seen her before,
but I can't place it.

196
00:14:12,123 --> 00:14:14,853
And she could be lying to us
about who...

197
00:14:16,194 --> 00:14:18,458
What the hell?

198
00:14:19,197 --> 00:14:20,528
JULIA:
Looks like a fire.

199
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,858
That's near the school.

200
00:14:33,912 --> 00:14:36,779
Hey! What the hell are you doing?

201
00:14:36,948 --> 00:14:38,074
What I have to.

202
00:14:38,983 --> 00:14:41,042
Otherwise, we're all dead.

203
00:15:17,622 --> 00:15:20,853
All she ever wanted to do
was get out of here.

204
00:15:24,462 --> 00:15:26,430
Maybe now Angie's finally free.

205
00:15:26,598 --> 00:15:28,156
Free?

206
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:29,891
She's dead.

207
00:15:30,368 --> 00:15:31,665
Don't try and cheer me up, okay?

208
00:15:31,836 --> 00:15:33,701
I'm sorry.
I was just trying to help you.

209
00:15:33,872 --> 00:15:35,305
Only one thing could do that.

210
00:15:36,841 --> 00:15:39,435
I wanna kill the person
who did this to her.

211
00:15:39,611 --> 00:15:41,909
I want them in pain.

212
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:45,049
More pain than they
ever thought was possible.

213
00:15:48,319 --> 00:15:51,811
What if that person's
right here under this roof?

214
00:15:52,157 --> 00:15:53,419
Big Jim?

215
00:15:53,591 --> 00:15:57,186
No, I went downstairs last night
when I couldn't sleep.

216
00:15:57,362 --> 00:15:59,353
He was crashed out on the couch.

217
00:15:59,531 --> 00:16:01,328
Not Big Jim, Joe.

218
00:16:01,499 --> 00:16:03,296
The girl we found.

219
00:16:04,235 --> 00:16:06,760
- Why would she hurt Angie?
- I don't know.

220
00:16:07,172 --> 00:16:10,835
But I heard the cops
found a shoeprint at the scene.

221
00:16:12,477 --> 00:16:13,501
A girl's shoeprint.

222
00:16:20,151 --> 00:16:22,449
JULIA:
Sorry we woke you.

223
00:16:25,156 --> 00:16:28,887
It would be really helpful
if you could remember something.

224
00:16:29,527 --> 00:16:30,994
Anything.

225
00:16:31,162 --> 00:16:32,652
Promise you'll protect me?

226
00:16:32,830 --> 00:16:34,161
You can trust me.

227
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:36,859
I was there.

228
00:16:37,502 --> 00:16:38,526
Last night.

229
00:16:38,703 --> 00:16:39,863
I saw it.

230
00:16:40,038 --> 00:16:41,972
You were at the school?

231
00:16:43,007 --> 00:16:45,202
I heard her scream.

232
00:16:45,376 --> 00:16:47,105
Why didn't you tell anyone?

233
00:16:47,278 --> 00:16:48,802
I was too scared.

234
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:51,505
I was afraid he'd come after me.

235
00:16:51,683 --> 00:16:53,241
He?

236
00:16:53,418 --> 00:16:55,716
Did you see a face?

237
00:16:55,887 --> 00:17:00,551
The sheriff found a young woman's
shoeprint in the hallway.

238
00:17:01,626 --> 00:17:05,585
- I think it's gonna match yours.
- They don't think I did it, do they?

239
00:17:05,763 --> 00:17:07,424
They're gonna find out
you were there.

240
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:10,762
I need you to tell me
why you were at the school.

241
00:17:11,502 --> 00:17:13,470
I don't know.

242
00:17:14,239 --> 00:17:17,731
Something made me go there.

243
00:17:20,812 --> 00:17:22,052
What the hell is going on here?

244
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:24,876
I had to stop the infestation
before it destroyed all the crops.

245
00:17:25,049 --> 00:17:26,812
- Infestation?
- Yes.

246
00:17:26,985 --> 00:17:28,111
Butterfly eggs.

247
00:17:28,286 --> 00:17:29,310
They're everywhere.

248
00:17:29,487 --> 00:17:31,567
When these eggs hatch some time
in the next 12 hours,

249
00:17:31,723 --> 00:17:34,385
the caterpillars inside will devour
absolutely everything in sight.

250
00:17:34,559 --> 00:17:36,239
- I thought they only eat milkweed.
- Yeah.

251
00:17:36,394 --> 00:17:38,191
Typically they do,
but I think the magnetism

252
00:17:38,363 --> 00:17:39,883
must have altered
their eating pattern.

253
00:17:40,031 --> 00:17:42,864
- So we lose the rest of this field?
- And all the surrounding fields.

254
00:17:43,034 --> 00:17:46,902
When they get through this one, they'll
move on and eat our entire food supply.

255
00:17:47,071 --> 00:17:48,368
So, what do we do?

256
00:17:48,539 --> 00:17:50,598
We need to burn everything.

257
00:17:50,775 --> 00:17:52,868
From the frontage road
to Langston's property line.

258
00:17:53,044 --> 00:17:55,911
That's where the infestation stops,
for now.

259
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:58,378
We'll save at least 50 percent
of the wheat that way

260
00:17:58,549 --> 00:18:01,143
and hopefully
we'll have enough to ration.

261
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:03,753
- This is a test.
- What makes you say that?

262
00:18:04,956 --> 00:18:08,756
You were there
when I offered myself on the gallows.

263
00:18:09,994 --> 00:18:12,258
It was the first test of many.

264
00:18:13,698 --> 00:18:17,190
I'm guessing the dome
wants me to prove myself.

265
00:18:17,468 --> 00:18:20,562
- What is he talking about?
- Himself.

266
00:18:20,738 --> 00:18:22,399
As usual.

267
00:18:22,573 --> 00:18:24,973
Come on, you never picked up
on his hero complex?

268
00:18:25,143 --> 00:18:28,306
Inflated ego or not,
they listen to him, don't they?

269
00:18:30,214 --> 00:18:35,516
Hey, Jim, burning half our food supply
doesn't sound like a solution to me.

270
00:18:35,687 --> 00:18:37,211
He's right.

271
00:18:38,156 --> 00:18:41,182
Most of these farmers have pesticide.
Can't we spray the fields with it?

272
00:18:41,359 --> 00:18:44,123
We'll never be able to cover that
much acreage before the eggs hatch.

273
00:18:44,295 --> 00:18:46,661
Think I might know
something that'll work.

274
00:18:50,802 --> 00:18:53,202
- Hey.
- Sam, we found the girl.

275
00:18:53,905 --> 00:18:55,463
Where was she?
I looked everywhere.

276
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,664
Hiding in the woods.

277
00:18:56,841 --> 00:18:59,605
I need to know if she said anything
to you before she left yesterday.

278
00:18:59,777 --> 00:19:01,301
Nothing.

279
00:19:02,013 --> 00:19:03,037
What's wrong?

280
00:19:03,214 --> 00:19:06,980
A young woman named Angie was
murdered last night at the high school.

281
00:19:11,889 --> 00:19:14,255
They found a woman's shoeprint.

282
00:19:14,425 --> 00:19:15,653
Probably hers.

283
00:19:16,127 --> 00:19:18,288
I seriously doubt that girl's a killer.

284
00:19:18,463 --> 00:19:21,193
That's what I wanna believe.
But maybe I'm too involved.

285
00:19:21,366 --> 00:19:24,301
- I wouldn't second-guess my gut.
- I got people telling me otherwise.

286
00:19:24,469 --> 00:19:25,800
I know how you feel.

287
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:30,407
But there was someone
I should have protected once.

288
00:19:30,575 --> 00:19:34,568
And maybe if I'd listened to my gut,
she'd still be here.

289
00:19:35,079 --> 00:19:38,173
Is this your sister,
the one who took her life?

290
00:19:38,349 --> 00:19:41,978
All this time, I'd been blaming Big Jim,
but the truth is,

291
00:19:42,153 --> 00:19:43,177
I could have done more.

292
00:19:43,955 --> 00:19:45,752
Big Jim's wife killed herself.

293
00:19:47,959 --> 00:19:51,520
- Oh, God, you're...
- Big Jim's brother-in-law.

294
00:19:52,063 --> 00:19:54,998
How is it possible
that everyone around me

295
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,963
is trapped in Big Jim's orbit?

296
00:19:57,135 --> 00:20:01,367
Well, now, hang on a second.
No one hates Big Jim as much as I do.

297
00:20:01,539 --> 00:20:04,804
He wasn't good to Pauline and Junior.
He was never there for them.

298
00:20:04,976 --> 00:20:08,639
Sam, you're practically
related to Big Jim.

299
00:20:09,514 --> 00:20:12,005
What happens when that starts
to mean something again?

300
00:20:12,183 --> 00:20:15,414
And what about my connection to you?
And this girl?

301
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:18,887
I wasn't sure
if I should show this to you.

302
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:30,731
I think there's something more
to this girl, to how we all fit together.

303
00:20:33,671 --> 00:20:36,162
My sister drew things.

304
00:20:37,308 --> 00:20:39,401
JULIA: This looks like her.
Pauline drew this?

305
00:20:40,044 --> 00:20:41,102
Twenty years ago.

306
00:20:44,048 --> 00:20:45,538
Belonged to Chuck Thomson,

307
00:20:45,716 --> 00:20:49,652
the, uh, flight school pilot
who crashed the day the dome fell.

308
00:20:50,988 --> 00:20:54,151
Looks like it's been sitting
round a while. Does it fly?

309
00:20:54,325 --> 00:20:56,589
It better, it's our only chance.

310
00:20:56,761 --> 00:21:00,527
Do I need to mention that no one's tried
to navigate the dome from the air yet?

311
00:21:00,698 --> 00:21:04,065
- You're not gonna be able to see it...
- I've flown this area plenty of times.

312
00:21:04,235 --> 00:21:05,497
You?

313
00:21:05,670 --> 00:21:08,332
You live in a town long enough,
you wear just about every hat.

314
00:21:08,506 --> 00:21:11,339
- Took lessons for search and rescue.
- Hey, seriously?

315
00:21:11,509 --> 00:21:13,875
Jim, I've flown
hundreds of missions.

316
00:21:14,045 --> 00:21:15,910
In some pretty tough places.

317
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:19,015
This plague was sent
as a test for me, Barbie.

318
00:21:22,553 --> 00:21:26,353
If I can't figure my own way out of this,
I don't deserve to lead this town.

319
00:21:32,597 --> 00:21:34,827
I didn't want her to be alone.

320
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,263
I understand.

321
00:21:38,202 --> 00:21:39,328
What's he doing here?

322
00:21:39,504 --> 00:21:42,701
Sam's one of the only people left
in town with any real medical training.

323
00:21:42,874 --> 00:21:44,501
I don't want anybody
touching Angie.

324
00:21:44,675 --> 00:21:45,995
JULIA:
We have to examine the body

325
00:21:46,143 --> 00:21:47,903
for evidence so we can find
whoever did this.

326
00:21:50,014 --> 00:21:52,141
Can you give us a sec?

327
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:55,644
Yeah. I'll go check on the girl.

328
00:21:58,155 --> 00:22:01,420
Look, I know I haven't
been there for you. I'm here now.

329
00:22:01,592 --> 00:22:03,787
Family's gonna be more important
in these days ahead.

330
00:22:03,961 --> 00:22:06,555
Sorry if family
doesn't mean much to me.

331
00:22:10,568 --> 00:22:14,026
I know it's been hard
since you lost your mom.

332
00:22:14,205 --> 00:22:17,663
And I wish you could have
known her like I did.

333
00:22:18,309 --> 00:22:21,767
She wasn't always
the confused woman you knew.

334
00:22:23,347 --> 00:22:26,009
- Do you ever see her?
- Like in a dream?

335
00:22:26,183 --> 00:22:29,311
Yeah. I did.

336
00:22:29,487 --> 00:22:32,217
Yesterday. Only it felt so real.

337
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:36,019
Probably the magnetic stuff
from the dome playing with your head.

338
00:22:36,661 --> 00:22:38,686
It messed me up.

339
00:22:39,297 --> 00:22:41,822
That's why I got drunk last night
and blacked out.

340
00:22:41,999 --> 00:22:43,660
I wasn't there for Angie.

341
00:22:44,702 --> 00:22:45,760
Never gets easier.

342
00:22:46,837 --> 00:22:48,771
Losing people.

343
00:22:49,273 --> 00:22:52,265
But you got to find a better way
of dealing with it than I did.

344
00:22:52,443 --> 00:22:55,469
I've been there, Junior,
I know how you feel.

345
00:22:57,081 --> 00:23:00,175
Is it possible to love someone so much
that you'd hurt them?

346
00:23:00,351 --> 00:23:02,114
Love can make you do crazy things,

347
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:06,383
but you'd never do anything violent
to the person you loved, would you?

348
00:23:06,557 --> 00:23:08,388
I don't remember anything
from last night,

349
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:10,618
but there's no way
I'd hurt Angie like that.

350
00:23:10,795 --> 00:23:12,626
She finally trusted me again.

351
00:23:12,797 --> 00:23:17,029
- Have any idea who'd do this to her?
- Of course. My father.

352
00:23:21,539 --> 00:23:23,097
Rebecca.

353
00:23:23,341 --> 00:23:26,674
Listen, we only got
one shot at this, okay?

354
00:23:26,844 --> 00:23:28,744
And we can't afford to risk it
just because

355
00:23:28,913 --> 00:23:34,112
someone wants to fuel their image.
So do me a favor, help me out.

356
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:37,647
Okay.

357
00:23:41,492 --> 00:23:42,754
Hey.

358
00:23:42,927 --> 00:23:45,020
Um, I think we should let Dale go up.

359
00:23:45,196 --> 00:23:46,959
I can handle this.

360
00:23:47,131 --> 00:23:51,534
I know, but it's dangerous
and Barbie is more experienced.

361
00:23:53,204 --> 00:23:56,537
Jim, the town's looking to you
right now, okay?

362
00:23:56,707 --> 00:23:59,972
They need a leader, not a martyr.

363
00:24:00,144 --> 00:24:03,170
- If anything happens up there, then...
- It won't.

364
00:24:04,115 --> 00:24:05,912
So, what do we got?

365
00:24:06,984 --> 00:24:08,704
Langston's fields
haven't been infected yet,

366
00:24:08,853 --> 00:24:11,913
so if we contain
the spraying to this quadrant...

367
00:24:28,105 --> 00:24:29,538
Phil.

368
00:24:30,174 --> 00:24:33,041
Joe, real sorry for your loss.

369
00:24:33,210 --> 00:24:35,178
We know who did it.
The girl we saw in the woods.

370
00:24:35,346 --> 00:24:37,546
I understand you're desperate
for answers, give it time.

371
00:24:37,682 --> 00:24:39,343
JOE:
We heard you found a footprint.

372
00:24:39,517 --> 00:24:42,350
So we took her shoe from the house
while she was resting.

373
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:45,080
Just see if it's a match.

374
00:24:46,190 --> 00:24:47,555
JIM:
I hope you're happy.

375
00:24:47,725 --> 00:24:49,989
Whole town's come out
to see your stunts.

376
00:24:50,161 --> 00:24:52,493
How about you just let me know
which way to turn

377
00:24:52,663 --> 00:24:54,494
after I drop this stuff over the crops?

378
00:24:54,665 --> 00:24:56,997
Veer a sharp left
over Hansen's fields,

379
00:24:57,168 --> 00:25:00,535
and three silos come up on you fast
after you rise over that break of trees.

380
00:25:00,938 --> 00:25:03,202
All right, let's do this.

381
00:25:12,283 --> 00:25:14,808
REBECCA:
He's getting too close to the dome.

382
00:25:17,588 --> 00:25:18,953
JULIA:
Phil, what are you doing?

383
00:25:19,123 --> 00:25:21,057
- Doesn't concern you, Julia.
- Like hell.

384
00:25:21,225 --> 00:25:23,352
The neighbors said you
dragged her off in a squad car.

385
00:25:23,527 --> 00:25:24,892
You can't do this.

386
00:25:25,062 --> 00:25:28,054
- I am holding her for questioning.
- On what grounds?

387
00:25:28,232 --> 00:25:30,496
We matched her shoeprint
to the one at the school.

388
00:25:30,668 --> 00:25:33,694
I know she was there, but a shoeprint
doesn't prove any more than that.

389
00:25:33,871 --> 00:25:35,236
And not that she's the murderer.

390
00:25:35,406 --> 00:25:37,897
You knew she'd been
at the crime scene? How?

391
00:25:39,176 --> 00:25:41,576
- She confided in me.
- When were you gonna tell the police?

392
00:25:41,746 --> 00:25:44,647
She says she saw a man do it.
You have to keep looking.

393
00:25:44,815 --> 00:25:48,444
You're lucky I'm not bringing you in
for harboring a suspect.

394
00:25:48,619 --> 00:25:50,450
Please, Julia. He'll find me in here.

395
00:25:50,621 --> 00:25:52,612
I'll get you out.

396
00:26:00,131 --> 00:26:01,792
What are you doing?

397
00:26:01,966 --> 00:26:03,729
I think my dad killed Angie.

398
00:26:03,901 --> 00:26:06,096
I just need to find something
that'll prove it.

399
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:08,204
It wasn't him, Junior.

400
00:26:08,372 --> 00:26:10,602
What if he had a reason to do it?

401
00:26:11,509 --> 00:26:13,374
What if he knew
Angie wanted him dead?

402
00:26:13,544 --> 00:26:15,068
It was the girl we saw in the woods.

403
00:26:15,246 --> 00:26:17,714
They found her bloody shoeprint
at the school.

404
00:26:19,984 --> 00:26:22,646
- Where is she now?
- Phil took her to jail.

405
00:26:24,355 --> 00:26:25,822
Okay.

406
00:26:28,125 --> 00:26:30,218
She deserves what Angie got.

407
00:26:32,329 --> 00:26:33,728
Don't you want that?

408
00:26:34,365 --> 00:26:36,390
For your sister?

409
00:26:42,173 --> 00:26:45,472
Sam, I'm gonna get that last field,
just up here ahead of me by the creek.

410
00:26:46,043 --> 00:26:48,341
- Last one.
REBECCA: Too close to the perimeter.

411
00:26:48,512 --> 00:26:51,481
Circle south, bring it back.
You gotta be running out of fuel.

412
00:26:52,149 --> 00:26:55,277
Hey, we'll burn it, we'll figure
something out, just get back here.

413
00:26:57,087 --> 00:27:00,420
If you get too close to that thing, we all
know what happens to electronics.

414
00:27:00,591 --> 00:27:01,888
It'll fry your systems.

415
00:27:02,059 --> 00:27:03,424
No, I'll take my chances.

416
00:27:03,594 --> 00:27:05,357
We got any obstructions
down there?

417
00:27:05,529 --> 00:27:07,588
Any power lines, windmills, silos?

418
00:27:07,765 --> 00:27:10,495
Only an impenetrable,
completely invisible dome.

419
00:27:11,268 --> 00:27:13,498
Hey, get out of there.

420
00:27:14,338 --> 00:27:16,033
You are only a hundred yards away.

421
00:27:16,540 --> 00:27:18,804
You won't be able to turn out of it.

422
00:27:21,278 --> 00:27:23,269
Damn it, Barbie, pull up, now.

423
00:27:31,722 --> 00:27:32,780
Engine's still running,

424
00:27:34,725 --> 00:27:36,989
but my wing's damaged,
I'm gonna bring it back in.

425
00:27:37,161 --> 00:27:38,594
[BEEPING]

426
00:27:38,762 --> 00:27:41,362
All right, I'm not gonna make
the airstrip, I'm dropping too fast.

427
00:27:41,498 --> 00:27:43,193
- I'm out of fuel.
- He's gonna crash.

428
00:27:44,702 --> 00:27:46,182
BARBIE:
I'm gonna put it in the trees.

429
00:27:46,337 --> 00:27:48,931
At least that way I'll be clear
of any of the people.

430
00:27:52,109 --> 00:27:53,406
Barbie, can you hear me?

431
00:27:53,577 --> 00:27:55,897
There's a switch under the right side
of the control panel.

432
00:27:56,046 --> 00:27:57,741
You need to flip it.
Barbie, listen to me.

433
00:27:57,915 --> 00:28:01,874
Reach under the right side and flip
the switch towards you, just do it.

434
00:28:02,052 --> 00:28:03,679
Trust me.

435
00:28:20,638 --> 00:28:22,518
What happened?
It's like I picked up extra fuel.

436
00:28:22,673 --> 00:28:26,234
Like it switched over to another tank.
Now I can land this thing.

437
00:28:46,096 --> 00:28:47,461
MAN 1:
Nice job.

438
00:28:50,868 --> 00:28:52,301
Yeah.

439
00:28:52,469 --> 00:28:54,096
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

440
00:28:54,638 --> 00:28:57,198
MAN 2: That's it, man.
WOMAN 1: He's good.

441
00:28:57,374 --> 00:28:59,035
MAN 3: Good work.
WOMAN 2: Yeah, Barbie.

442
00:28:59,209 --> 00:29:00,938
MAN 1: That's it, thanks, man.
- Thank you.

443
00:29:01,111 --> 00:29:04,137
Hey, good job.

444
00:29:07,985 --> 00:29:09,384
Reserve tank, huh?

445
00:29:09,553 --> 00:29:12,647
Well, came in handy when I had
to make few trips out of Chester's Mill.

446
00:29:13,357 --> 00:29:15,621
Those drug runs
you used to do with Coggins.

447
00:29:15,793 --> 00:29:17,784
That's all ancient history.

448
00:29:19,463 --> 00:29:22,694
Well, I got to say,
I never expected to be the one

449
00:29:22,866 --> 00:29:24,333
thanking you for saving my life.

450
00:29:25,536 --> 00:29:30,235
Yeah, well, meet the new Big Jim.

451
00:29:31,275 --> 00:29:32,833
Right.

452
00:29:35,012 --> 00:29:38,413
From the angle of the impact,
the killer must have struck like this:

453
00:29:38,582 --> 00:29:40,516
The angle doesn't necessary tell us
their height.

454
00:29:41,118 --> 00:29:43,643
Well, whoever did this
had to have a lot of strength.

455
00:29:45,990 --> 00:29:48,515
You think I'm nuts
for defending someone I don't know?

456
00:29:48,692 --> 00:29:52,856
I think you're brave
taking all this on as your responsibility.

457
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,998
And a little nuts.

458
00:29:56,500 --> 00:30:00,163
Looks like Angie got a piece
of whoever did this to her.

459
00:30:02,406 --> 00:30:04,772
SAM:
Those bruises are lividity.

460
00:30:04,942 --> 00:30:06,170
Blood pools after death.

461
00:30:06,744 --> 00:30:08,473
JULIA:
Those are the fingertips of a hand.

462
00:30:09,146 --> 00:30:11,114
- A big hand.
- A man's.

463
00:30:11,281 --> 00:30:12,475
Definitely not a girl.

464
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:17,042
We gotta get down to the station.
Get that poor girl released.

465
00:30:27,398 --> 00:30:29,798
Why'd you do it?
Why'd you kill Angie?

466
00:30:29,967 --> 00:30:30,991
I didn't.

467
00:30:32,403 --> 00:30:33,529
It wasn't me.

468
00:30:33,704 --> 00:30:35,968
We know you're lying.
Tell us the truth, now.

469
00:30:38,675 --> 00:30:40,199
Go ahead.

470
00:30:42,179 --> 00:30:43,612
Do it.

471
00:30:46,517 --> 00:30:47,575
Well, then I will.

472
00:30:51,522 --> 00:30:52,819
You don't wanna do this.

473
00:30:53,357 --> 00:30:55,587
- You took my sister from me.
- Please.

474
00:30:57,828 --> 00:31:00,262
Joe. Joe, stop. It wasn't her.

475
00:31:00,431 --> 00:31:03,366
We found bruising on Angie's arm.
From a man's hand.

476
00:31:03,534 --> 00:31:05,866
- A man?
- Joe.

477
00:31:06,036 --> 00:31:07,128
Put the gun down.

478
00:31:07,304 --> 00:31:08,828
Did you hear me?

479
00:31:09,006 --> 00:31:12,669
She saw Angie, but there wasn't
enough time to save her.

480
00:31:13,410 --> 00:31:15,344
She didn't do it, Joe.

481
00:31:30,127 --> 00:31:35,224
It's two days in a row now that girl
owes her life to you and that Sam guy.

482
00:31:35,966 --> 00:31:37,763
It's good you made it
to the cell in time.

483
00:31:38,068 --> 00:31:39,468
I don't think Joe would've done it.

484
00:31:40,037 --> 00:31:42,232
I'm really glad
we didn't have to find out.

485
00:31:42,406 --> 00:31:45,102
Jim will probably tell people
he saved your life today.

486
00:31:45,275 --> 00:31:49,439
He didn't have to tell me about
that reserve tank. But he did.

487
00:31:50,747 --> 00:31:54,706
Yesterday, we save his life,
he can barely utter a thank-you.

488
00:31:54,885 --> 00:31:57,251
I think in some strange way he tried.

489
00:31:57,421 --> 00:31:59,252
A few words
does not change the fact

490
00:31:59,423 --> 00:32:02,153
that all he cares about
is his folklore status.

491
00:32:02,326 --> 00:32:03,806
And he's not the only one fueling it.

492
00:32:03,961 --> 00:32:06,486
Rebecca has been
talking him up all over town.

493
00:32:06,897 --> 00:32:10,628
She's also the one who discovered the
whole crop problem in the first place.

494
00:32:10,801 --> 00:32:13,998
But a few science textbooks is not
gonna solve what's happening here.

495
00:32:14,171 --> 00:32:16,503
She doesn't know everything
about this dome.

496
00:32:16,673 --> 00:32:18,163
And we do?

497
00:32:18,342 --> 00:32:22,802
I'm sorry, but the dome let Big Jim live
and an innocent girl die.

498
00:32:22,980 --> 00:32:26,313
It does not care
what happens to us down here.

499
00:32:27,918 --> 00:32:30,250
I don't understand
anything that's happening.

500
00:32:31,855 --> 00:32:33,914
But I'm starting to feel like
I'm losing you.

501
00:32:34,791 --> 00:32:37,055
Like I'm losing your trust.

502
00:32:37,227 --> 00:32:38,626
Why?

503
00:32:38,795 --> 00:32:42,390
Because I need to agree
with you to trust you?

504
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:51,168
And Sam Verdreaux?

505
00:32:52,643 --> 00:32:54,338
He agrees?

506
00:32:59,917 --> 00:33:00,975
- Andrea.
- Jim.

507
00:33:01,151 --> 00:33:02,709
How are you?

508
00:33:02,886 --> 00:33:04,444
How are you?

509
00:33:05,255 --> 00:33:06,279
- Hey.
- Hey.

510
00:33:06,456 --> 00:33:07,787
How are you holding up?

511
00:33:07,958 --> 00:33:12,054
- Angie was one of your students.
- When she made it to class.

512
00:33:13,764 --> 00:33:15,755
I always liked her.

513
00:33:16,667 --> 00:33:20,330
It must be terrible for your son
knowing the killer's still out there.

514
00:33:20,504 --> 00:33:23,564
I'm sure it's too hard
for him to be here.

515
00:33:24,007 --> 00:33:26,441
Yeah, I wish
I could do more for him.

516
00:33:26,610 --> 00:33:29,306
- You do plenty.
MAN: Julia, so sorry.

517
00:33:29,479 --> 00:33:31,709
REBECCA: I hate that he's
getting to be the hero.

518
00:33:32,349 --> 00:33:34,977
If they only knew you saved him.

519
00:33:37,187 --> 00:33:38,518
It's not about one day.

520
00:33:39,223 --> 00:33:43,216
Heroes leave behind a good story,
but a great leader leaves a legacy.

521
00:33:45,329 --> 00:33:47,763
You don't really believe
the dome chose me to lead, do you?

522
00:33:47,931 --> 00:33:49,899
I believe Chester's Mill chose you.

523
00:33:51,168 --> 00:33:53,193
And they're gonna need us.

524
00:33:53,370 --> 00:33:54,928
You especially today.

525
00:33:56,440 --> 00:34:00,171
Well, I don't think Joe wants me
anywhere near this church today.

526
00:34:00,344 --> 00:34:03,643
Joe is not the only one
who's lost someone.

527
00:34:08,185 --> 00:34:10,050
They're about to start
and Joe isn't here.

528
00:34:10,821 --> 00:34:13,813
He can't miss
his own sister's funeral.

529
00:34:14,524 --> 00:34:16,389
I'll find him.

530
00:34:30,841 --> 00:34:32,468
Hey, kiddo.

531
00:34:34,878 --> 00:34:37,142
Everybody's waiting for you
back at the church.

532
00:34:37,314 --> 00:34:38,804
I'm looking for her bracelet.

533
00:34:38,982 --> 00:34:42,645
She always wore it.
And she didn't have it on when...

534
00:34:44,454 --> 00:34:45,716
You think she left it here?

535
00:34:45,889 --> 00:34:48,449
She lost it somewhere
and she'd want it.

536
00:34:48,625 --> 00:34:51,560
- I know she'd want it.
- No.

537
00:34:53,497 --> 00:34:55,590
She'd wanna know
that you were okay.

538
00:34:58,902 --> 00:35:00,767
You always came first.

539
00:35:01,338 --> 00:35:02,965
Then why did she leave me?

540
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,631
What was she doing
at the high school all alone?

541
00:35:07,244 --> 00:35:09,109
I don't understand
who could do this to her.

542
00:35:09,279 --> 00:35:10,678
Hey.

543
00:35:14,351 --> 00:35:16,376
I promise you...

544
00:35:18,021 --> 00:35:19,989
...we're gonna catch
whoever did this.

545
00:35:20,657 --> 00:35:22,022
You can't promise that.

546
00:35:23,226 --> 00:35:24,250
You don't know.

547
00:35:25,595 --> 00:35:28,860
- You don't know anything.
- No, I do know.

548
00:35:31,234 --> 00:35:32,861
I lost someone.

549
00:35:34,171 --> 00:35:35,832
And I was so mad.

550
00:35:37,774 --> 00:35:41,266
I didn't wanna go to some church
and watch the show.

551
00:35:43,146 --> 00:35:45,910
You know, all those people,
maybe they cared...

552
00:35:47,384 --> 00:35:49,318
...or maybe they didn't.

553
00:35:52,489 --> 00:35:54,923
But there's not a day...

554
00:35:58,128 --> 00:36:03,566
...that I don't wish that I'd taken
the chance to say goodbye.

555
00:36:08,238 --> 00:36:10,365
I'm not ready to.

556
00:36:19,249 --> 00:36:21,046
I know you're not.

557
00:36:22,152 --> 00:36:24,814
But I'm gonna be right here,
all right?

558
00:36:25,555 --> 00:36:27,352
You're not alone.

559
00:36:29,092 --> 00:36:33,654
Our losses over the past few days
are almost too much for us to bear.

560
00:36:34,164 --> 00:36:39,261
Our beloved sheriff, Linda Esquivel,
and now an innocent young woman,

561
00:36:39,436 --> 00:36:42,337
with her whole life ahead of her...

562
00:36:43,640 --> 00:36:45,198
...snatched away from us.

563
00:36:46,510 --> 00:36:49,206
No one has any answers.

564
00:36:49,379 --> 00:36:51,108
No one can tell us why.

565
00:36:53,016 --> 00:36:55,883
But I promise you, I will never rest

566
00:36:56,186 --> 00:37:00,452
until Angie gets the justice
she deserves.

567
00:37:00,757 --> 00:37:02,987
JUNIOR:
Angie's bracelet.

568
00:37:18,241 --> 00:37:22,177
There's almost nothing
that can make us understand

569
00:37:22,345 --> 00:37:25,746
why Angie was taken so soon.

570
00:37:25,916 --> 00:37:28,749
She was a daughter, a sister.

571
00:37:29,519 --> 00:37:31,646
She had big dreams.

572
00:37:33,957 --> 00:37:37,984
Whatever differences
we may have had in the past,

573
00:37:38,161 --> 00:37:41,824
we need to be there
for each other now.

574
00:37:41,998 --> 00:37:43,625
ALL:
Amen.

575
00:37:46,536 --> 00:37:52,736
You know, for most of my life,
I've only had faith in one thing:

576
00:37:55,045 --> 00:37:57,172
That I could sell a car
to anybody who came on my lot.

577
00:37:57,347 --> 00:37:59,178
[ALL CHUCKLE]

578
00:37:59,349 --> 00:38:00,839
But these past few days,

579
00:38:01,251 --> 00:38:07,918
we've had a storm of epic proportions,
an infestation, you know, a plague.

580
00:38:08,091 --> 00:38:09,581
Why?

581
00:38:09,993 --> 00:38:15,932
Because we are being tested by some
power that is bigger than any of us.

582
00:38:16,099 --> 00:38:18,829
And after these trials,
I've found my faith.

583
00:38:19,002 --> 00:38:21,266
That we are all here for a reason.

584
00:38:21,805 --> 00:38:23,670
And what I wanna know

585
00:38:24,741 --> 00:38:27,107
- is what do you have faith in?
- It's you, Jim.

586
00:38:27,277 --> 00:38:28,505
MAN 1: Jim.
MAN 2: You.

587
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:32,400
That means a lot, I appreciate that,
but it's not about me.

588
00:38:32,549 --> 00:38:36,451
It's about us.
We have to pull together.

589
00:38:37,687 --> 00:38:41,214
Look at them,
they would do anything for him.

590
00:38:42,359 --> 00:38:44,623
Thank you, Jim.
Such inspiring words.

591
00:38:44,794 --> 00:38:46,625
Thank you, Andrea.

592
00:38:49,366 --> 00:38:51,334
They loved you.

593
00:38:51,501 --> 00:38:53,264
Well, I meant it.

594
00:38:53,670 --> 00:38:56,730
- Every word.
- Mm. Well, we're gonna need it.

595
00:38:56,907 --> 00:38:58,340
Angie's death was bittersweet.

596
00:38:59,409 --> 00:39:03,140
- Excuse me?
- Well, Angie was taken too early,

597
00:39:03,313 --> 00:39:04,837
but spared what's to come.

598
00:39:05,015 --> 00:39:07,711
I'm afraid you'll need to keep
that eulogy on hand.

599
00:39:07,884 --> 00:39:10,011
What are you talking about?

600
00:39:10,587 --> 00:39:13,818
We saved the crops today. I've taken
inventory of our other supplies which...

601
00:39:13,990 --> 00:39:15,630
You've taken inventory
of the wrong thing.

602
00:39:16,393 --> 00:39:17,485
We're the problem, Jim.

603
00:39:18,261 --> 00:39:23,528
It's us. There are too many people
in here for our limited resources.

604
00:39:25,135 --> 00:39:26,534
We can't all survive.

605
00:39:28,305 --> 00:39:30,170
[BANGING ON DOOR]

606
00:39:33,143 --> 00:39:34,542
I'm coming.

607
00:39:46,122 --> 00:39:49,421
Junior. What's going on?

608
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:51,684
I think I did it.

609
00:39:54,097 --> 00:39:56,224
I think I killed Angie.
